---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import RelatedLinks from '../../components/RelatedLinks.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Superweapons & Boss Previews"
  description="Every confirmed superweapon and boss encounter in Ace Combat 8: Wings of Theve, starting with the Land Battleship — a 450-meter ground weapon revealed in the June 2026 trailer."
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Superweapons' }]} />
  <article class="container article">
    <span class="eyebrow">A returning series staple</span>
    <h1>Superweapons &amp; Boss Encounters</h1>
    <p>
      Massive superweapons — colossal, multi-phase enemies that dwarf standard aircraft — are
      a signature of the Ace Combat series, and Wings of Theve continues the tradition. Here's
      every one Bandai Namco has confirmed so far.
    </p>

    <div class="card boss-card">
      <span class="eyebrow">Confirmed in the June 2026 State of Play trailer</span>
      <h2>The Land Battleship</h2>
      <div class="boss-card__stats">
        <div><span class="mono label">Length</span><span class="mono value">~450 meters</span></div>
        <div><span class="mono label">Type</span><span class="mono value">Ground-based superweapon</span></div>
        <div><span class="mono label">Location</span><span class="mono value">Theve (FCU capital)</span></div>
      </div>
      <p>
        The Land Battleship is a massive vehicular weapon encroaching on Theve, destroying
        surrounding skyscrapers and everything in its path as it advances. Bandai Namco has
        confirmed it plays a key role in the story — described as "holding the key to the
        story" — rather than being a one-off spectacle encounter.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the reveal footage, Joker Flight engages it by dodging its main gun attacks while
        looking for openings to strike. Given Wings of Theve's new damage system — where
        hostile targets can now take damage anywhere, not just marked weak points — expect
        this fight to reward sustained, mobile engagement over hunting for a single weak spot
        like in older entries.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card callout">
      <p class="mono eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">More bosses expected</p>
      <p style="margin:0;">
        Bandai Namco hasn't confirmed the full roster of superweapons yet — with a "largest
        online mode" and a campaign built around escalating stakes, more are almost certainly
        coming. We'll add each one here as it's revealed, and build out full attack-pattern
        breakdowns once we can verify them in the actual game.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedLinks items={[
    { href: '/new-mechanics', label: 'New Mechanics', desc: 'The no-weak-point-only damage system that changes how boss fights play out.' },
    { href: '/story', label: 'Story & Setting', desc: 'Why Theve — and what\'s at stake when the Land Battleship attacks it.' },
    { href: '/aircraft', label: 'Aircraft List', desc: 'Pick the right aircraft before you take on a superweapon.' },
  ]} />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .article { padding: 56px 0 80px; max-width: 760px; }
  .article > p { font-size: 0.98rem; }
  .boss-card { margin: 24px 0; }
  .boss-card h2 { margin: 6px 0 16px; }
  .boss-card p { font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .boss-card__stats {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 24px;
    margin: 14px 0 18px;
    padding: 14px 0;
    border-top: var(--border-thin);
    border-bottom: var(--border-thin);
  }
  .boss-card__stats > div { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
  .boss-card__stats .label { font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--text-secondary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .boss-card__stats .value { color: var(--hud-amber); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .callout { margin: 24px 0; }
</style>
